    "# Get started"

  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Get forest cover change from TMF\n",
    "\n",
    "The function `.get_fcc()` can be used to download forest cover change from the Tropical Moist Forest product. We will use the Reunion Island (isocode \"REU\") as a case study."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 1,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "import os\n",
    "\n",
    "import ee\n",
    "import geefcc\n",
    "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n",
    "from matplotlib.colors import ListedColormap\n",
    "import matplotlib.patches as mpatches\n",
    "import cartopy.crs as ccrs\n",
    "import rioxarray"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 2,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Initialize GEE\n",
    "ee.Initialize(project=\"forestatrisk\", opt_url=\"https://earthengine-highvolume.googleapis.com\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 3,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Download data from GEE\n",
    "if not os.path.isfile(\"out_tmf/forest_tmf.tif\"):\n",
    "    geefcc.get_fcc(\n",
    "        aoi=\"REU\",\n",
    "        years=[2000, 2010, 2020],\n",
    "        source=\"tmf\",\n",
    "        tile_size=0.5,\n",
    "        output_file=\"out_tmf/forest_tmf.tif\",\n",
    "    )"
   ]
  },

   "execution_count": 4,

    "# Computing the sum\n",
    "fcc_tmf = forest_tmf.sum(dim=\"band\")\n",
    "fcc_tmf"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 6,
   "metadata": {
    "scrolled": true
   },
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Colors\n",
    "cols=[(255, 165, 0, 255), (227, 26, 28, 255), (34, 139, 34, 255)]\n",
    "colors = [(1, 1, 1, 0)]  # transparent white for 0\n",
    "cmax = 255.0  # float for division\n",
    "for col in cols:\n",
    "    col_class = tuple([i / cmax for i in col])\n",
    "    colors.append(col_class)\n",
    "color_map = ListedColormap(colors)\n",
    "\n",
    "# Labels\n",
    "labels = {0: \"non-forest in 2000\", 1:\"deforestation 2000-2009\", 2:\"deforestation 2010-2019\", 3:\"forest in 2020\"}\n",
    "patches =[mpatches.Patch(facecolor=col, edgecolor=\"black\", label=labels[i]) for (i, col) in enumerate(colors)]"
   ]
  },

  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Compare with forest cover change from GFC"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 8,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Get data from GEE\n",
    "if not os.path.isfile(\"out_gfc_50/forest_gfc_50.tif\"):\n",
    "    geefcc.get_fcc(\n",
    "        aoi=\"REU\",\n",
    "        years=[2001, 2010, 2020],  # Here, first year must be 2001 (1st Jan)\n",
    "        source=\"gfc\",\n",
    "        perc=50,\n",
    "        tile_size=0.5,\n",
    "        output_file=\"out_gfc_50/forest_gfc_50.tif\",\n",
    "    )"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 9,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Load data\n",
    "forest_gfc = rioxarray.open_rasterio(\"out_gfc_50/forest_gfc_50.tif\")\n",
    "fcc_gfc = forest_gfc.sum(dim=\"band\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 10,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "",
      "text/plain": [

   "source": [
    "# Plot\n",
    "fig = plt.figure(figsize=[7, 5])\n",
    "ax = fig.add_axes([0, 0, 1, 1], projection=ccrs.PlateCarree())\n",
    "raster_image = fcc_gfc.plot(ax=ax, cmap=color_map, add_colorbar=False)\n",
    "plt.title(\"Forest cover change 2001-2010-2020, GFC\")\n",
    "labels = {0: \"non-forest in 2001\", 1:\"deforestation 2001-2009\", 2:\"deforestation 2010-2019\", 3:\"forest in 2020\"}\n",
    "patches =[mpatches.Patch(facecolor=col, edgecolor=\"black\", label=labels[i]) for (i, col) in enumerate(colors)]\n",
    "plt.legend(handles=patches, bbox_to_anchor=(1.05, 1), loc=2, borderaxespad=0.)\n",
    "plt.show()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Comparing forest cover in 2020 between TMF and GFC"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 11,
   "metadata": {
    "scrolled": true
   },
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Computing difference and sum\n",
    "forest_diff = forest_tmf.sel(band=3) - forest_gfc.sel(band=3)\n",
    "forest_sum = forest_tmf.sel(band=3) + forest_gfc.sel(band=3)\n",
    "forest_diff = forest_diff.where(forest_sum != 0, -2)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 12,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Colors\n",
    "cols=[(10, 10, 150, 255), (34, 139, 34, 255), (200, 200, 0, 255)]\n",
    "colors = [(1, 1, 1, 0)]  # transparent white for -2\n",
    "cmax = 255.0  # float for division\n",
    "for col in cols:\n",
    "    col_class = tuple([i / cmax for i in col])\n",
    "    colors.append(col_class)\n",
    "color_map = ListedColormap(colors)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 13,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Labels\n",
    "labels = {0: \"non-forest tmf, non-forest gfc\", 1:\"non-forest tmf / forest gfc\",\n",
    "          2:\"forest tmf / forest gfc\", 3:\"forest tmf, non-forest gfc\"}\n",
    "patches =[mpatches.Patch(facecolor=col, edgecolor=\"black\", label=labels[i]) for (i, col) in enumerate(colors)]"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 14,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {

   "source": [
    "# Plot\n",
    "fig = plt.figure(figsize=[7, 5])\n",
    "ax = fig.add_axes([0, 0, 1, 1], projection=ccrs.PlateCarree())\n",
    "raster_image = forest_diff.plot(ax=ax, cmap=color_map, add_colorbar=False)\n",
    "plt.title(\"Difference between TMF and GFC for forest cover in 2020\")\n",
    "plt.legend(handles=patches, bbox_to_anchor=(1.05, 1), loc=2, borderaxespad=0.)\n",
